<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="detail-n">detail <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'diːteɪl/    美 /'diːteɪl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] 细节；琐事 [U] 详情 ：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tell me more details about the job. 
多告诉我一些关于这项工作的具体情况。</p><footer>2008 江西</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-detail">in detail</h3>
<p>1.<strong>详细地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Planning is good as it decides in detail how we do what we want to do.
做计划的好处在于它详细地规定了如何做我们想做的事。</p><footer>2016 浙江书面表达</footer></div>

<h3 id="go-into-details">go into detail(s)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>详细叙述；逐一说明：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I can’t go into details now; it would take too long.
我现在不能细说，太费时间了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>detailed /'diːteɪld/ adj   </p>
<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>We’d better discuss everything <strong><em>_</em></strong> (详细地) before we work out the plan.   （2011 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. in detail  </p></div>